This paper proposes a new method for visual perception tasks such as object detection and tracking, which are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of the kernel trick, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of fast Fourier transform (FFT), which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
